text: Lannea transulta is a species of plant in the family Anacardiaceae. It is endemic to Yemen. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical dry forests and subtropical or tropical dry shrubland. ==References== Category:Endemic flora of Socotra transulta Category:Near threatened plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Taxa named by Isaac Bayley Balfour
